The cutting surface is naturally ground to avoid injury. However, a possible slight ripple of the cutting surface cannot always be avoided!In the first few minutes, the wine bottle is briefly fogged from the inside, which is normal, after a short warm-up phase, the water vapor should have evaporated.The wind light has an approximate weight of approx. 1080g and is therefore very stable. The concrete base has of course undercut felt gliders to ensure protection against scratching of the surfaces on which the wind light stands. At the same time, the oxygen supply of the candle is ensured by a hole in the foot and the chimney effect.Half the glass bottle should be touched during operation if necessary, only at the extremely lower part as the upper one naturally gets hot.I have this windlight for all sorts of occasions like e.g. Weddings, birthdays designed for the garden or simply as evening underwriting in the house. name: Necklace Triskele Triple Spiral Wood Burned
description: Unique men's or ladies wooden necklace.Triple spiral(Druidism): Derived from the Greek word "Triskeles" meaning "three legs", the Triskele or Triple Spiral is a complex ancient Celtic symbol. Often referred to by many as a Triskelion, its earliest creation dates back to the Neolithic era, as it can be seen at the entrance of Newgrange, Ireland. The Triskele gained popularity in its use within the Celtic culture from 500BC onwards. This archaic symbol is one of the most convoluted to decipher as symbolists believe it is reflective of many areas of culture from the time.1)The motion of action, cycles, progress, revolution and competition.2)Life-death-rebirth, spirit-mind-body, mother-father-child, past-present-future, power-intellect-love and creation-preservation-destructionIt’s thought that through the combination of these two areas we gain one meaning of the Celtic triskele. It is believed to represent a tale of forward motion to reach understanding. However, this is thought not to be the only meaning, as it is also believed to represent three Celtic worlds; the spiritual world, the present world and the celestial world. Like the ancient Trinity knot, the number 3 holds a special symbolism within the triskele.Material:Wood: Beech WoodCord:  Cotton Waxed CordVarnish: Odorless Wood Varnish for children's toysApproximate Dimensions:Size:  35mm x 35mm x ~5mmCord Size: AdjustablePlease note that this item is handmade, so there may be small differences comparing with the photo.If you have any inquiries, please don’t hesitate to contact me.
